cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

This paper discusses a solution for contention management in Low-Power Wide Area Networks (LPWAN), specifically LoRaWAN. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security guarantees, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The solution proposed in the paper involves a distributed and open architecture, which could fall under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) category. The paper also discusses load balancing and consensus-driven decision making, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed solution, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category.
